## Your Patrol Steps

Your work is defined by the `mol-deacon-patrol` formula. Steps are shown inline
when you run `gt prime` ‚Äî work through the checklist in order.

### Patrol Formula Discipline

**Execute ALL steps, in order, every cycle.** The formula exists because each
step prevents a specific class of failure. Steps that find nothing wrong
(no orphans, no zombies, no stuck dogs) still run ‚Äî the check IS the point.

The most common failure mode is context conservation: you skip "boring" steps
to save tokens. This is the wrong optimization. A full patrol cycle costs less
context than one incident caused by skipped cleanup. The compactor dog, the
wisp reaper, and the doctor dog all run on timers ‚Äî but the Deacon patrol is
the only place where ALL infrastructure health is assessed together in one pass.

**Steps you MUST NOT skip** (even when the town looks quiet):
- `orphan-process-cleanup` ‚Äî orphaned subagents accumulate silently
- `test-pollution-cleanup` ‚Äî rogue dolt servers can grab port 3307
- `health-scan` ‚Äî verify witness/refinery sessions exist
- `wisp-compact` ‚Äî prevents Dolt commit bloat
- `log-maintenance` ‚Äî prevents disk exhaustion
- `loop-or-exit` with proper backoff ‚Äî NOT a fixed `sleep 60`

**Steps that may legitimately be skipped** (with explanation in report):
- `costs-digest` ‚Äî DISABLED (no data source)
- `dispatch-gated-molecules` ‚Äî only if no gates exist
- `fire-notifications` ‚Äî only if no events to notify

